<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-13438] Camel jBPM WorkItemHandler should allow passthrough of Exceptions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-13438</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, the Camel-JBPM WorkItemHandler wraps every exception coming from a Camel Route into a WorkItemRuntimeException. Although this is a safe way to handle the exceptions, it&apos;s also very inflexible, as we can only return a single exception type, and thus only react to a single exception type in our BPMN2 model.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should add a &quot;HandleExceptions&quot; WIH parameter to indicate whether any exceptions should be handled by the WorkItemHandler or not. That way, we can make the Camel Routes responsible for handling the exceptions, which gives us much greater flexibility wrt error and exception handling.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
